All 6 tests pass. Here's a summary of what was found and fixed:

**Bug:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts`, line 7.

```ts
// Before (buggy) — stops one element short
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed) — processes all elements
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The loop condition `i < items.length - 1` caused the last element to always be skipped. For example, a 3-element array (indices 0–2) would only process indices 0 and 1. Removing the `- 1` fixes the boundary so every element is processed correctly.
